Package com.net2plan.interfaces.simulation

Provides a set of classes for the online simulator tool.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ICombinedEventGenerator
    Abstract class providing an event generator that is able to combine existing event generators into a common one.
    ICombinedEventProcessor
    Abstract class providing an event processor that is able to combine existing event processors into a common one.
    IEventGenerator
    Abstract class that must be inherited so that an event generator can be executed inside the Online network simulation tool included within Net2Plan.
    IEventProcessor
    Abstract class that must be inherited so that an event processor can be executed inside the Online network simulation tool included within Net2Plan.
    SimEvent
    Class representing a simulation event.
    SimEvent.DemandAdd
    This class represents the request to add a new Demand.
    SimEvent.DemandModify
    This class represents the request to modify an existing Demand.
    SimEvent.DemandRemove
    This class represents the request to remove an existing Demand.
    SimEvent.LinkAdd
    This class represents the request to add a new Link.
    SimEvent.LinkModify
    This class represents the request to modify an existing Link
    SimEvent.LinkRemove
    This class represents the request to remove an existing Link.
    SimEvent.NodesAndLinksChangeFailureState
    This class represents the request to modify the failure state of multiple links and nodes.
    SimEvent.RouteAdd
    This class represents the request to add a new Route.
    SimEvent.RouteModify
    This class represents the request to modify an existing Route.
    SimEvent.RouteRemove
    This class represents the request to remove and existing Route.
    SimEvent.SegmentAdd
    This class represents the request to add a new Protection Segment.
    SimEvent.SegmentRemove
    This class represents the request to remove an existing Protection Segment.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SimEvent.DestinationModule
    Module that will receive the associated event.
